title: fix(ngScenario): disable animations during e2e tests
body:
The current tutorial (step-12) fails its e2e tests as the animations are not completing before the
expectations are checked.  This fixes that and is generally the right thing to do for other e2e
test situations.

title: Improve $http's caching documentation
body: Make possibility to pass custom cache instance to $http more obvious.

milestone.title: Docs Only
milestone.description:
Documentation only pull requests and issues can go in here.

This is a place to put PRs that are purely updating the documentation - i.e. no code changes.

When triaging I was putting such PRs into the next milestone, which at the moment would be 1.2.2 but I found that since these doc-fixes were not blocking releases, it was hiding how much real work was needed before the milestone was ready for the release.  

In effect, I created a parallel track for documentation updates.  Then when I had the time, I could sit down and knock off a dozen of these PRs at my leisure.

title: fix(ngInclude & ngView): Conditionally autoscroll after animation
body:
We need to wait until animations have added the content to the document before
trying to autoscroll to anchors that may have been inserted.

title: fix(ngdocs): add ids to headers in tests
body:
Doc.markdown (in /docs/src/ngdoc.js) gives headers ids, yet headers don't have ids in the specs.
That's causing the tests "ngdoc markdown should replace text between two [pre] tags", and "ngdoc TAG @description should support multiple pre blocks" to fail when building the documentation.
This change adds ids to headers in the specs to match the behavior of Doc.markdown.

title: ngRepeat: insert end comment only after last element, not after each iterated item
body:
This caused a subtle bug in angular-sortable directive: when moving elements
between lists, previousNode was a comment, which doesn't have the .parentNode
attribute so the $animate.enter function tried to call insertBefore of a null.

Moreover, it looks bad that 'end ngRepeat' comment appears after every iterated
node, it should be just at the end of the repeat block.

body: Putting ng-hide inside the directive to be handled as its own function and adding an increment function to be passed to the directive as a delegate of the on-close function. This better illustrates functionality that might be passed to the directive, as well as which functionality the directive should handle itself.

title: Correcting example of isolated scope function binding
body: Moving the ng-hide to be in the scope outside the directive in stead of inside and calling the hideDialog function from the controller in stead of just switching the variable boolean value.

title: fix(ngdocs): remove duplicate header ids
body:
Headers with ids are being given additional id attributes.
That's causing the test "ngdoc usage overview should supress description heading" to fail while building the documentation.
This prevents additional id attributes from being added to a header that already has an id.

title: fix(httpBackend): IE undefined response in legacy standards mode
body:
Fixes issue #4738. IE10 using IE8 document standards mode has
responseType but response in undefined, responseText has a value in this
scenario.
Solution is to try and fallback to responseText if reponse is empty.
